    {
      "ts": "1708797554.209779",
      "human_ts": "2024-02-24 11:59:14 CST",
      "user_id": "U011U13BEPR",
      "user_label": "Chris Williams (U011U13BEPR)",
      "text": "Although not with a lot of clarity from driving at 70+ mph, the pavement is failing at the longitudinal joint and not in the wheel paths from truck loading.",
      "subtype": null,
      "thread_ts": null,
      "edited_ts": null,
      "deleted": false,
      "attachments": []
    },
    {
      "ts": "1708797703.023239",
      "human_ts": "2024-02-24 12:01:43 CST",
      "user_id": "U011U13BEPR",
      "user_label": "Chris Williams (U011U13BEPR)",
      "text": "To share my answer to my son of why the pavement is red. It is from the use of quartzite from South Dakota that contains some iron. And it is really important to have skid resistance on roads especially very high volume roads like I-80 which quartzite provides.",
      "subtype": null,
      "thread_ts": null,
      "edited_ts": null,
      "deleted": false,
      "attachments": []
    },
    {
      "ts": "1708797835.381549",
      "human_ts": "2024-02-24 12:03:55 CST",
      "user_id": "U011U13BEPR",
      "user_label": "Chris Williams (U011U13BEPR)",
      "text": "So we can understand the requirements the Iowa DOT understanding their specifications and what is on their roadway network. Skid resistance is a requirement and color is not. Longer life is highly desirable and embedded in their specifications.",
      "subtype": null,
      "thread_ts": null,
      "edited_ts": null,
      "deleted": false,
      "attachments": []
    },
    {
      "ts": "1708797910.064229",
      "human_ts": "2024-02-24 12:05:10 CST",
      "user_id": "U011U13BEPR",
      "user_label": "Chris Williams (U011U13BEPR)",
      "text": "Again, the pavement is failing at the longitudinal joint. Our Vitala+ emulsion would have extended this pavement for many years. Now we are going to see it reconstructed over a 2-year period with a lot of construction costs and tens of thousands if not more in work zone traffic delays. And Vitala+ can go over paint stripping without needing new paint.",
      "subtype": null,
      "thread_ts": null,
      "edited_ts": null,
      "deleted": false,
      "attachments": []
    },
    {
      "ts": "1708797956.136029",
      "human_ts": "2024-02-24 12:05:56 CST",
      "user_id": "U011U13BEPR",
      "user_label": "Chris Williams (U011U13BEPR)",
      "text": "What do we know and believe are most important to the Iowa DOT?",
